				<li id="16518822" class="cmnt-root" data="15" data-d="1647424482000"><ul class="comments"><li class="comment-box"><div class="avatar"><img src="/images/avatar.png" alt="" /><div class="comment-username">Anonymous</div></div><div class="comment"><div class="title"><span class="txt-subject"></span><input style="display: none;" class="txt-subject-ed"><span class="right cmt-ui"><a href="https://fextralife.com/forums/t576503/Dragonfire" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">16 Mar 2022 05:54</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a class="report-post" href="https://fextralife.com/forums/report.php?f=193&p=16518822" rel="nofollow" target="_blank" title="report this post"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-flag" aria-hidden="true"></span></a></span></div><p class="txt-comment">Don&apos;t let people convince you that this is a bad spell; you just have to use it properly.  The AoE cone is great for taking out incoming hordes as long as you have the time to cast it.  Some bosses and invaders also find the cone difficult to evade, making it an effective counter to some enemies who might be difficult to take out with more efficient spells.  Channeling will drain your FP quickly, but will also dish out very rapid damage, in a long range, and a bit wider than you might expect.<br/><br/>I don&apos;t have the Dragon Communion Seal, but I do use the Roar Medallion to boost its damage.</p><textarea style="display: none;" class="txt-comment-ed"></textarea><div class="clearfix"><a role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#zz-16518822" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Reply</a><a id="btnExpandComment" role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#replies-16518822" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Replies (<span class="replies">2</span>)</a><div class="vote pull-right"><section class="t-up"><span></span><p>20</p><i class="add">+1</i></section><section class="t-down"><span></span><p>5</p><i class="sub">-1</i